        <div class="sec1">
             <img src="about.jpg"><p>
                Lionel Messi, commonly known as Leo Messi, is an Argentine professional soccer player widely regarded <br> as one of the greatest footballers of all time. Born on June 24, 1987, Messi spent the majority of his career  <br> at FC Barcelona, where he showcased extraordinary talent,  remarkable dribbling skills, and an exceptional <br> goal-scoring ability. His agility, vision, and precise left foot have earned him numerous accolades, including  <br> multiple Ballon d'Or awards for the best player in the world. In 2021, Messi moved to Paris Saint-Germain (PSG) <br> after spending over two decades at Barcelona, continuing to mesmerize fans worldwide with his unparalleled <br> mastery of the beautiful game.</p>
        
    </div>

    <div class="sec2">
             <img src="about1.jpg"><p>
                Lionel Messi's legendary status in football stems from his unparalleled skill set, consistent excellence, <br> and profound impact  on the sport. His record-breaking goal-scoring prowess, dazzling dribbling abilities, and <br> exceptional vision have set him apart as a once-in-a-generation talent. Messi's numerous individual awards, <br> including multiple  Ballon d'Or titles, underscore his  dominance in the game. Beyond statistics, his influence transcends <br> the field, inspiring millions globally with his humility, sportsmanship, and dedication. His long-standing tenure <br> at FC Barcelona, marked by numerous titles and magical moments, solidified his legacy as an icon of the sport,<br> earning him a revered place among football's all-time greats.</p>
        
